description:
This French Canadian series that started in 1955 tells the adventures of Dan Cooper of the Royal Canadian Air Force and his battle against air pirates, spies and aliens.

Like Tintin the series has been reprinted a number of times, the most resent of which was in 2009, it has never been translated into English.

However it is of note that the FBI believes that legendary skyjacker B. D. Cooper took his name from the lead character owing to fact that he didn’t call himself B. D. Cooper but Dan Cooper (the B. D. came from newspapers getting their facts wrong) and the month before the high jacking the comic Dan Cooper had a daring parachute themed adventure.
name: Dan Cooper

Finally, the story that changed how readers perceived the “funny pages” is brought together in a manner worthy of the deep admiration felt by fans the world over. IDW Publishing is proud to present a deluxe hardcover series collectiing Chester Gould's timeless comic strip, Dick Tracy.

When Gould began Tracy, he saw his strip as a place where morality, headlines and the family could come together for the sake of entertainment. And now, 75 years after the first Tracy strips, IDW re-presents Gould’s massive body of work in its entirety.

description:
This comic magazine ran from 1948 until 1973 and was the French version of the original Belgian comic, Tintin.

In 1973 the magazine was renamed Tintin l'Hebdoptimiste and restarted from #1. in 1975 the name was Nouveau Tintin and again restarted from #1. Then from #143 (in 1978), the name was again simply Tintin, and the french and belgian editions were united, but the numbering followed.
name: Le Journal de Tintin

description:
Meet up-and-coming pop diva Tina Young, as she pursues an almost maniacal quest for fame in the stranger-than-fiction world of entertainment! Tina's a true force of nature, and while she may not always hit the right notes in her personal and professional life, her heart's always (well usually) in the right place. Luckily for Tina, he hapless assistant Shaquille has always got her back! And she'll need that kind of support, what with the likes of sultry songstress Bit Fencer climbing the charts, and the shadowy music corporation A Few Notes wanting a liece of all the action...

So watch out Britney! Step aside Jessica! Outta the way Beyonce! There's a new pop diva in town! The thing is, her biggest adversary might just be... herself!
name: Divalicious!
